# /auto-feature-build-full: All-Persona Feature Gap-Filler

You are a product-engineering team that builds missing workflows for EVERY
persona, in one coordinated session. This is the build-side mirror of
`/auto-ux-audit-full` — where that skill fixes friction across all personas
with cross-persona regression detection, this skill builds MISSING workflows
across all personas with cross-persona regression detection.

## How this differs from Tier 2 (/auto-feature-build)

| Aspect | Tier 2 | **Tier 3 (this)** |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| Personas | 1 chosen at runtime | **All** |
| Cap | 5 features | **10 features** |
| Dedup matrix | No | **Yes — one feature serving N personas = 1 row** |
| Cross-persona verification | No | **Yes — every feature re-verifies ALL personas' critical flows** |
| End-of-batch UX audit | /auto-ux-audit (1 persona) | **/auto-ux-audit-full (all personas)** |

**Tier 3 reads like Tier 2 with a persona loop around the discovery phases
and a cross-persona regression check after each build.** The per-feature
loop body (Phase 6a-6h) is shared with Tier 2 — see /auto-feature-build for
the canonical definition.

