## Phase 1: Load ALL personas

### 1A. Read the shared registry

```bash
cat .gstack/ux-audit/personas.md 2>/dev/null
```

If the registry exists: load every persona. No runtime selection.

### 1B. If the registry is missing

Inline /ux-audit Phase 1 discovery logic for the FULL set (not just one
persona). Write the complete registry to `.gstack/ux-audit/personas.md`.

### 1C. Determine execution order (mirrors /auto-ux-audit-full 1E)

Personas are processed in this order:

1. **Highest frequency first** — daily > weekly > occasional > first-time
2. **Highest permission first** within the same frequency — admin before
   regular user
3. **Unauthenticated last** — visitor/anonymous personas

Rationale: auth-heavy, high-permission personas establish the scaffolding
(auth, permissions, list views) that lower-frequency personas depend on.
Build the root features once; lower-tier personas reuse them.

