## Phase 3.5: Cross-Persona Dedup Matrix (NEW)

Multiple personas may share the same missing feature. An admin needing
"password reset" and a member needing "password reset" is the SAME feature;
building it once serves both.

### 3.5A. Build the dedup matrix

For every gap report entry across all personas, compute a **dedup key**:

```
dedup_key = (route-prefix, primary-verb, primary-resource)
```

Examples:
- `(admin/users, reset, password)` — admin password reset
- `(account, reset, password)` — member self-serve password reset
- `(admin/users, edit, role)` — admin edits user role

### 3.5B. Merge rules

- **Same dedup key across personas → 1 feature row** with
  `serves_personas: [P1, P2, ...]`
- **Same key BUT divergent acceptance criteria → keep as separate rows**
  (safer to build twice than to merge two different specs into one plan)
- **Near-miss keys (same route, different verb) → keep separate** unless
  the acceptance criteria overlap

### 3.5C. Write the matrix

Write to: `.gstack/feature-build/cross-persona-matrix-{DATETIME}.md`

Format:

```
# Cross-Persona Feature Matrix — {DATETIME}

| Feature ID | Name | Dedup key | Serves personas | Source gap reports |
|-----------|------|-----------|------------------|---------------------|
| F-X-001   | Password reset | (admin/users, reset, password) | [P1] | gap-report-P1 |
| F-X-002   | User list with search | (admin/users, list, user) | [P1, P2] | gap-report-P1, gap-report-P2 |
| F-X-003   | Account settings | (account, edit, profile) | [P2] | gap-report-P2 |

## Dropped (as duplicates)
| From | Merged into | Reason |
|------|-------------|--------|
| F-P2-003 | F-X-002 | Same dedup key, compatible criteria |
```

