## Phase 5: GATE 1 — Scope Approval (10-feature cap, MANDATORY)

Present the unified DAG as an indented tree. Warn loudly if > 20 features.

```
## Feature Build Queue — Proposal (all personas)

Total features discovered: {N}
Personas: {count} ({P1, P2, ...})
[⚠️ WARNING if N > 20]

Feature DAG (deduped across personas):
  1. F-X-001  Critical   Login     serves=[P1,P2]
  2. F-X-002  Critical   User list serves=[P1]     (depends on F-X-001)
  3. F-X-003  Important  Password reset serves=[P1,P2] (depends on F-X-002)
  ...

Default recommendation: top 5 features (by priority + breadth of persona
coverage).
Hard cap: 10 features per run.
```

AskUserQuestion:
- A) Build top 5 (recommended)
- B) Build all capped at 10
- C) Let me pick specific features
- D) Cancel

Populate the queue file with approved rows. STOP until user responds.

